It would appear, therefore, that the third penny of the pleas is the final remnant of the judicial functions of the earl, and is originally due to the Frankish empire. Whether this imperial institution reached the England of Henry II through William the Conqueror, or whether it came with earlier importations from the same source, admits as yet of no exact determination.
